HEADWORD: Firebrand
<hw>Fire"brand`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
piece of burning wood.</def> <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who inflames factions, or causes contention and
mischief; an incendiary.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>firebrat</ent>⟦br⟧
